.TH TG2SIP-WEBRTC 1 "July 2026" "tg2sip-webrtc" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tg2sip-webrtc \- Telegram <-> SIP voice gateway using tgcalls (WebRTC)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tg2sip-webrtc
.RI [ config-file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tg2sip-webrtc
bridges Telegram calls, via TDLib and tgcalls (WebRTC), to a SIP PBX via
PJSIP, in both directions: incoming Telegram calls can be forwarded to a
SIP extension, and SIP can place outgoing calls to Telegram contacts.
.PP
Before the daemon can log in and run unattended, a TDLib session must
exist. Create one with
.BR gen_db (1).
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is resolved in this order:
.IP \(bu
an explicit path given as the first command-line argument;
.IP \(bu
.I /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/tg2sip.conf
if it exists;
.IP \(bu
.I tg2sip.conf
in the current working directory (development fallback).
.PP
See the comments in
.I /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/tg2sip.conf
for all available settings.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/tg2sip.conf
Configuration file (a dpkg conffile).
.TP
.I /var/lib/tg2sip-webrtc/db.sqlite
TDLib session database, created by
.BR gen_db (1).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gen_db (1)
.PP
.I https://github.com/vladonv/tg2sip-webrtc
